<p><b>IV. HUMAN RIGHTS SITUATIONS THAT REQUIRE 
THE COUNCIL&#8217;S ATTENTION 
</b></p>
<p><b>A. Situation of human rights in the Democratic 
People&#8217;s Republic of Korea 
</b></p>
<p>300. At the 23rd meeting, on 13 March 2008, the Special Rapporteur on the situation of human 
rights in the Democratic People&#8217;s Republic of Korea, Vitit Muntarbhorn, presented his report 
(A/HRC/7/20). 
</p>
<p>301. At the same meeting, the observer for the Democratic People&#8217;s Republic of Korea, as the 
concerned country, made a statement. 
</p>
<p>302. During the ensuing interactive dialogue at the same meeting, the following made 
statements: 
</p>
<p> (<i>a</i>) Representatives of States members of the Council: Cuba, Indonesia, Japan, Slovenia 
(on behalf of the European Union), Republic of Korea, United Kingdom of Great Britain and 
Northern Ireland; 
</p>
